Imports System Imports System.IO Imports TotalAgility.Sdk Imports Agility.Server.Scripting.ScriptAssembly
Namespace MyNamespace
Public Class Class1
<StartMethodAttribute()> Public Sub Method1(ByVal sp As ScriptParameters) ' ' TODO: Add start method code here '
Dim SessionID as String = sp.InputVariables("SPP_SYSTEM_SESSION_ID") Dim FolderID as String = sp.InputVariables("FOLDERID") Dim DocumentID as String = sp.InputVariables("DOCUMENTID")
Dim DocumentNumber as String = sp.InputVariables("DOCUMENTNUMBER") Dim DocumentType as String = sp.InputVariables("DOCUMENTTYPE")
Dim Path as String = sp.InputVariables("STORAGEPATH")
Dim ErrorMessage as String = ""
Dim ds = New CaptureDocumentService Dim FileStream as Stream Dim fsWrite As FileStream
Dim bRead As BinaryReader Dim b As Byte Dim bWrite As BinaryWriter
Try
FileStream = ds.GetDocumentRenditionsFile(SessionID, DocumentID, "1","tiff") ' Removed PageID
Path = Path + FolderID + "\" + DocumentNumber + " - " + DocumentType + "\"
'check if folder exist if not create it If Not Directory.Exists(Path) Then Directory.CreateDirectory(Path) End If
Path = Path + DocumentType + ".tiff"
'create a fileStream instance to pass to BinaryWriter object fsWrite = New FileStream(Path, FileMode.CreateNew, FileAccess.Write)
'create binary writer instance bWrite = New BinaryWriter(fsWrite)
'create instance of binary reader bRead = New BinaryReader(FileStream)
'set the file pointer to the start of the file bRead.BaseStream.Seek(0, SeekOrigin.Begin)
'loop until can no longer read bytes from file Do While True
Try
'read next byte and advance reader b = bRead.ReadByte
Catch Exit Do End Try
'write byte out bWrite.Write(b)
Loop
'close the reader bRead.Close()
'close the writer bWrite.Close()
'close the file streams FileStream.Close() fsWrite.Close()
Catch ex As Exception ErrorMessage = "Error : " & ex.Message sp.OutputVariables("ERRORMESSAGE") = ErrorMessage End Try
End Sub End Class End Namespace
